{"lemma":"طُولُ","slug":"طُولُ","root":"ط.#.ل","root_slug":"ط-_-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-_-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"طُول","root":"طول","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":17},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27342","n27343","n27344","n27345","n27346","n27355","n27362"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8F%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of طَالَ (ṭāla) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"length","examples":[{"text":"وَلَا تَمْشِ فِي ٱلْأَرْضِ مَرَحًا ۖ إِنَّكَ لَن تَخْرِقَ ٱلْأَرْضَ وَلَنْ تَبْلُغَ ٱلْجِبَالَ طُولًا"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"longitude"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"long duration"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"condition of being long-suffering"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"merit"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wealth"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"power"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bounty"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"duration of life, duration, while"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"absence"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lengthen"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to relax the tether"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grant a respite or delay"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be long at a thing"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to tarry, to delay"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be backward"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/tˤuːl/","/tˤawl/","/tˤaw.wa.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27342","headword_ar":"طَوْلٌ","root":"Twl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[is originally an inf. n.: (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAla Ealayohi","text_ar":"طَالَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and, used as a simple subst.,] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beneficence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bounty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a benefit, a favour, a boon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a gift."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 58.) ―         -b2-  And, (O, K, TA,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAy^ilN","text_ar":"طَايِلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAy^ilapN","text_ar":"طَايِلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Excellence, excess,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superabundance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ability:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"competence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ampleness of circumstances:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superiority,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ascendancy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lifulaAnK EalaY","text_ar":"لِفُلَانٍ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK TawolN","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ طَوْلٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To such a one belongs excellence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superabundance, above such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O. [And the like is said in the Mgh.]) And it is said in the Kur [iv. 29],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamano lamo yasotaTiEo minokumo TawolFA","text_ar":"وَمَنْ لَمْ يَسْتَطِعْ مِنْكُمْ طَوْلًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano yanokiHa A@lmuHoSanaAti","text_ar":"اَنْ يَنْكِحَ ا@لمُحْصَنَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And such of you as is not able to obtain superabundance so that he may marry the free women,"},{"kind":"text","text":"let him marry a female slave; (Mgh;) i. e. such as is not able to give the dowry of the free woman, (Mgh, O, TA,) as expl. by Zj. (Mgh, TA.) In the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tawolu AlHur~api","text_ar":"طَوْلُ الحُرَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the former word is originally the inf. n. of the verb in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAla EalayohaA","text_ar":"طَالَ عَلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ he benefited her; ” because, when one is able to give the dowry of the free woman, and pays it, he benefits her: or, as some of the lawyers says, this phrase means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The superabundance of the means of sustenance that suffices for the marrying of the free woman,"},{"kind":"text","text":"agreeably with a saying of Az: or, as some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Twl","text_ar":"طول"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"competence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the phrase is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawolN","text_ar":"طَوْلٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY AlHur~api","text_ar":"اـِلَى الحُرَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ampleness of wealth such as supplies the means of attaining to the free woman:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawolN EalaY AlHur~api","text_ar":"طَوْلٌ عَلَى الحُرَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ability, for the marrying of the free woman:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) Esh-Shaabee is related to have used the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~awolu A_ilaY AlHur~api","text_ar":"الطَّوْلُ اـِلَى الحُرَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in like manner are I'Ab and Jábir and Sa'eed Ibn-Jubeyr. (Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iY AlT~awoli","text_ar":"ذِى الطَّوْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur xl. 3 means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Possessor of all-sufficiency,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of superabundance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of bounty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Possessor of power:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of bounty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneficence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwluw AlT~awoli","text_ar":"اُولُو الطَّوْلِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minohumo","text_ar":"مِنْهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur ix. 87 means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Those, of them, who are possessors of superabundance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of opulence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiwalN","text_ar":"طِوَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter half, in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","TA","O","K","Mgh","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n27343","headword_ar":"طُولٌ","root":"Twl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[is originally an inf. n.: (see 1, first sentence:) and, used as a simple subst.,] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Length;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tallness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"height; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaroDN","text_ar":"عَرْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiSarN","text_ar":"قِصَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTowaAlN","text_ar":"اَطْوَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) it is in man and other animals, and in inanimate things: (TA:) in real things, or substances; and also in ideal things, or attributes, as time and the like. (Er-Rághib, TA.) [One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaEahu TuwlFA","text_ar":"قَطَعَهُ طُولًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlT~uwli","text_ar":"بِالطُّولِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut it lengthwise."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"utmost extent"},{"kind":"text","text":"of time. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^ukal~imuhu Tuwla Ald~ahori","text_ar":"لَا اُكَلِّمُهُ طُولَ الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ahori","text_ar":"الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaAla","text_ar":"طَوَالَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, * TA,) both meaning the same, (S, O, TA,) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not speak to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during the utmost extent of time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA.) ―         -b3-  [In geography, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"longitude"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a place: pl. as above.] ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiwalN","text_ar":"طِوَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["M","TA","Msb","S","O"]},{"entry_id":"n27344","headword_ar":"طَوَلٌ","root":"Twl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Length in the upper lip"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the camel, (M, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beyond the lower."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n27345","headword_ar":"طُوَلٌ","root":"Twl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiwalN","text_ar":"طِوَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwlaY","text_ar":"طُولَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTowalu","text_ar":"اَطْوَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27346","headword_ar":"طِوَلٌ","root":"Twl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", for which ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tiwal~N","text_ar":"طِوَلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in poetry, (S, O, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiyalN","text_ar":"طِيَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", for which also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tiyal~N","text_ar":"طِيَلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in poetry, (K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawiylapN","text_ar":"طَوِيلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, O, K,) but this is disapproved by Az, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiTowalN","text_ar":"تِطْوَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tether;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rope that is extended for a horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"similar beast, and attached to which he"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1897},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pastures:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rope with which the leg of such a beast is bound:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long rope thus used:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one binds him, holding its extremity, and letting the beast pasture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which one of the two ends is bound to a stake, and the other to the fore leg of a horse, in order that he may go round about bound thereby, and pasture, and not go away at random."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) An ex. of the first of these words occurs in a verse of Tarafeh cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vinoYN","text_ar":"ثِنْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O.) And it is said in a trad. that when a man of an army alights in a place, he may debar others from the extent of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tiwal","text_ar":"طِوَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"of his horse. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroxaY lahu AlT~iwala","text_ar":"اَرْخَى لَهُ الطِّوَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He relaxed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slackened, to him the tether"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means [also] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he left him to his own affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rxw","text_ar":"رخو"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAla Tiwaluka","text_ar":"طَالَ طِوَلُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tiyaluka","text_ar":"طِيَلُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tiyluka","text_ar":"طِيلُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuwluka","text_ar":"طُولُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuwaluka","text_ar":"طُوَلُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaAluka","text_ar":"طَوَالُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiyaAluka","text_ar":"طِيَالُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, O, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tawoluka","text_ar":"طَوْلُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy life"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has become long;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may thy life become long"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (ISk, S, O, K: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiylapN","text_ar":"طِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thine absence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy tarrying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy flagging in an affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) Tufeyl says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^ataAnaA falamo nadofaEohu A_i*o jaA='a TaAriqFA\n                      \n                     \n                        faA@nozili ↓ \n      waqulonaA lahu TaAla Tawoluka"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came to us, and we did not repel him since he came as a nightly visiter, and we said to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy case in respect of the length of the journey and the endurance of travel"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has been long, therefore alight thou:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the right reading may be ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuwluka","text_ar":"طُولُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is better known]: or, as some relate it, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tiyluka","text_ar":"طِيلُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [It is also said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiwalN","text_ar":"طِوَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. [or rather a coll. gen. n.] of which the sing. [or n. un.] is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiwalapN","text_ar":"طِوَلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in like manner, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiyalN","text_ar":"طِيَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiyalapN","text_ar":"طِيَلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","Lth","TA","ISk","A"]},{"entry_id":"n27355","headword_ar":"طِوَلٌّ","root":"Twl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiwalN","text_ar":"طِوَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27362","headword_ar":"طُوَّلٌ","root":"Twl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the aquatic kind, having long legs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K"]}]}}